fields.name: Cranberry Snack
fields.comment:
Hoi Windmillers!

I'm happy to pronounce you that we're excited to register our unusual team for the greatest tournament in europe.

We're Frisbee-maniacs from all over the world based on fun, spirit and mixed-ulitmate. The team was founded 2009 at Windmill Windup and is called Cranberry Snack!
Our players are french, dutch, german, american, australian, canadien, kiwi's, finns, irish...
We're friends and open-minded people who picking up players in europe they love ultimate but dont have a fix team...travelleres, hedonists and frisbee maniacs.
There are only two simple rules to get into the team...they must be good-looking and talented ;) 
In the end we are all connected by the spirit and the joy for frisbee in a wonderful green-minded team in pink jerseys. 
Needless to say that we're bringing home-baked cranberry cookies, Cranberry Likeur and other stuff for the spirit circle.

Since than we wrote many songs, for example:

"common over have some fruit, get into the chewing mood. Digestin under bright blue sky, common let your spirits fly..."

and of course our own version of Zombie by The Cranberrys!  


Beside of ultimate we love the tournament and the people who organize it with an extraordinary passion. It's huge, unique and a great way to see again all the crazy ultimate people from europe. Like a home coming in a living room. We love the swiss draw, the level of the games and 3 days of ultimate.


We really want to join the windmill community 2012 again!

Wish you all great achievements with the organization!

Hartelijke groeten van de Cranberries!
Klaus Walther
- Cranberry Snack -

fields.name: Rebel Ultimate
fields.comment: Rebel Ultimate are the two time defending Irish Mixed Club Champions. A core group of our players won UK Mixed College Nationals earlier this year. Rebel are looking to improve our experience of playing competitive Mixed Ultimate abroad. As a result we have signed up for Mixed Tour in the UK and are hoping to compete in the Mixed Division at Windmill Windup.
